events.150: Damascus became a Roman provincial city under Trajan
events.400: Temple of Jupiter built by the Romans
events.613: Sasanian captured Damascus during the Byzantine–Sasanian War of 602–628
events.634: Arab conquest of Damascus under Khalid ibn al-Walid
events.715: Great Mosque built by Al-Walid I by converting the church of St John the Baptist constructed by Arcadius
events.1260: Kitbuga, a confidant of the Mongol Ilkhan Hulagu, captured Damascus
events.1516: Ottomans under Selim I conquered Damascus from the Mamluks
events.1832: Captured by Ibrahim Pasha of Egypt
events.1840: Return of the city to Turkish domination, when the Egyptians were driven out of Syria
events.1860: Massacre; the Moslem population rose against the Christians
events.1918: October: Arab troops led by Emir Feisal, and supported by British Armed Forces, capture Damascus, ending 400 years of Ottoman rule
events.1920: July: French Armed Forces occupy Damascus, forcing Feisal to flee abroad
events.1961: September: Discontent with Egyptian domination of the United Arab Republic prompts a group of Syrian Army officers to seize power in Damascus and dissolve the union
events.1977: Higher Institute for Dramatic Arts founded
events.2011: March: Protest; crackdown. Syrian civil war begins
events.2012: May: Syrian Armed Forces recapture the entire city of Damascus
events.-965: Ezron, King of Aram-Zobah conquers Damascus
events.-843: Hazael assassinated Ben-Hadad I and made himself king of Damascus
events.-112: Damascus fell to Antiochus IX Cyzicenus
